    "narrative": "The clear anchor for the lineup today is **Corbin Carroll**, boasting an elite 87.14 efficiency score. He draws a favorable matchup against Martin, whose 4.68 xERA is the most exploitable among our high-confidence starters. **Corbin Carroll**\u2019s projected output is bolstered significantly by an optimal spot in the #3 hole and a strong xwOBA profile that suggests a breakout game is imminent. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** is a high-upside play at 75.75; the combination of a massive 14% park boost and the extreme vulnerability of Waldron (7.83 xERA) provides the perfect storm for a productive afternoon. We are also leaning on **Giancarlo Stanton** (61.78) and **Jose Caballero** (64.17) to capitalize on a platoon advantage against Tolle, whose 4.01 xERA is manageable enough to expect multi-hit or extra-base potential from our lower-order bats.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision today was the exclusion of **Brice Turang**, whose 45.53 score was respectable but ultimately didn't crack the threshold against the brutal matchup provided by Skubal. While **Brice Turang**\u2019s elite speed profile usually earns him a spot for stolen base upside, Skubal\u2019s 2.71 xERA and high hold rate against base stealers effectively neutralized that utility. We opted instead for **Kyle Karros** (59.58) in the UTIL slot to capture the park-adjusted offensive explosion expected against Waldron. Risk remains on the periphery: **Seiya Suzuki** (50.54) faces a tough outing against a 3.02 xERA arm, and **James Wood** (53.19) is facing a difficult hurdle in Ritchie. Both were kept in the lineup due to order positioning, but they carry the highest volatility if they fail to navigate their respective matchups early.",
